# Foundry Deployment

## Setup

```bash
curl -L https://foundry.paradigm.xyz | bash
foundryup
forge init my-project
```

## Deployment Script

Create `script/Deploy.s.sol`:

```solidity
// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
pragma solidity ^0.8.24;

import {Script} from "forge-std/Script.sol";
import {MyContract} from "../src/MyContract.sol";

contract DeployScript is Script {
    function run() external {
        uint256 deployerKey = vm.envUint("PRIVATE_KEY");
        vm.startBroadcast(deployerKey);
        new MyContract(constructorArg);
        vm.stopBroadcast();
    }
}
```

## Deploy

```bash
forge script script/Deploy.s.sol --rpc-url $RPC_URL --broadcast --verify
```

## Key Flags

- `--broadcast` — actually send transactions (dry-run without it)
- `--verify` — verify on Etherscan after deployment
- `--resume` — resume an interrupted deployment
- `--slow` — send transactions one at a time
- `--etherscan-api-key` — API key for verification

## Quick Deploy (no script)

```bash
forge create src/MyContract.sol:MyContract --rpc-url $RPC_URL --private-key $PRIVATE_KEY --constructor-args arg1 arg2
```

Use `forge create` for one-off deploys. Use `forge script` for repeatable, multi-contract deployments. Verify after deployment via [[ethereum/contract-deploy/verify]]. Ensure your [[ethereum/wallets]] is funded with enough ETH for [[ethereum/gas#estimation]].
